reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than the traditional Power Strip
reviews.reviewText: This is an excellent power strip. It has numerous outlets which are configured with generous space around each one so it does not matter how large the plugs or bricks are. It's light weigh and has on/off switch for each column of receptacles. Well thought out and the 10 ft cord is excellent.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This power strip was a great addition to our living room. I used to have a surge, protector plugged into another surge protector to reach. The outlet was behind the couch and nothing was long enough to reach the table, where we needed the extra plug ins. This surge protector works perfectly with added features. I can easily turn off any unused side and it also supplies us with the needed USB ports and 12 outlets (8 more than we had!). The stand-up feature also frees up some space on the table. This was a great purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the product.
reviews.reviewText: Love the spacing between plugs. Enough plugs for all my office electronics. Love the separate on and off switches, allows me to control power consumption. Love the cord length. Not yet had to use USB. Sturdy product, good profile and working great, so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Have the power
reviews.reviewText: Cord is a good length. I like that each side has it's own power switch and you can turn items completely off when not in use. Turn off those not-in-use wall-warts. The ultimate in surge protection control, if you over-worry (This unit surge-protects, too.) or unplug things when you are out. The built in USB adds convenient utility. I leave a cord in it so I can just walk up and plug my phone or tablet right in when I need to. It is 4-sided, so it needs a little space to use every plug. But you know what shape you are getting when you buy this. Works well in my late-50s kitchen, with it's limited receptacles. Could be just a little more 'solid'. 4.7 stars. "For Traveling" gets one star. (What a silly 'feature' to rate.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Gets the job done!
reviews.reviewText: I hate clutter, and I detest a bunch of electrical cords on the floor. I bought one of these for my bedroom stuff (clock radio, lamp, cable TV/DVR, Roku, etc.) and it's sitting atop my console. All cords off the floor (had em plugged into a standard power strip before, and it drove me crazy getting under the cabinet, if I had to reset the Roku device, or reboot my DVR (spent way to much time on the floor!). NOW, everything's accessible!I liked the idea so much, I bought one for my office (wi-fi modem, lamp, lamp timer, voip phone modem, landline, etc.) and what a joy! The four outlet sides operate independently, so if you don't have to use all four sides of the tower, ya just don't turn em all on (I'm using only 3), and you save electricity. Great product. Got both mine in black. Loving the extra organization this gives me, not to mention, getting all my ducks (cords) in a row. :~) Wish I'd done this a lot sooner!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Let me start off by saying, the power cable is long enough I could probably put this device on my roof and have a little left over to circle up and put a cable wrap on. I only use 2 or 3 plugs at a time (Don’t plug space heaters into anything but the wall LADIES) and the usb ports are an amazing addition. I can’t think of anything that would make it better, especially for the price. It’s charged devices that others wouldn’t, and I love that you can toggle the power off to the unit and to each side.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Have had this a while. It works just as described and handles multiple power cords (computer, lights, printer, etc.) with no problem. Size is smaller than my last one which is great for me. Very pleased with it.
